cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI 

The paper discusses multimodal machine translation, which involves drawing information from multiple modalities such as speech and visuals. This topic falls under the intersection of several subfields in computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Given the emphasis on language translation, cs.CL is the most likely category, followed by cs.CV due to the use of visual modalities. The other categories are also relevant due to the use of machine learning and AI techniques, as well as the focus on multimodality.
